findings.description:
In ProjectLinksTab.jsx lines 90-102, the GitHub metadata fetching uses a sequential 'for' loop to fetch repository information. If there are multiple GitHub repos in the links, they are fetched one at a time instead of in parallel.

for (const { owner, repo, key } of toFetch) {
  await getRepositoryInfo({ owner, repo }); // Waits for each to complete
}

This causes unnecessary delays. If there are 5 repos, and each takes 200ms, the total time is 1000ms instead of 200ms with parallel fetching.

findings.code_snippet:
(async () => {
  for (const { owner, repo, key } of toFetch) {
    try {
      const resp = await getRepositoryInfo({ owner, repo });
      // Sequential - waits for each request
    }
  }
})();

findings.recommendation:
Use Promise.all or Promise.allSettled to fetch all repos in parallel:
const promises = toFetch.map(async ({ owner, repo, key }) => {
  try {
    const resp = await getRepositoryInfo({ owner, repo });
    if (!cancelled) setGhMeta(prev => ({ ...prev, [key]: { data: resp?.data ?? resp ?? {}, loading: false, error: null } }));
  } catch (err) {
    if (!cancelled) setGhMeta(prev => ({ ...prev, [key]: { data: null, loading: false, error: err } }));
  }
});
await Promise.allSettled(promises);

